    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1960-11-10T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1960-11-10T00:00:00-05:00" n="42"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d42">
                <head>42. Memorandum for the Record<note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d42fn1">Source:
                        National Security Council, Intelligence Files, <gloss target="#t_NSC_1"
                            >NSC</gloss> 5412/2 Special Group, Minutes and Agendas, 1960. Secret;
                        Eyes Only.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>Washington</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian"
                            when="1960-11-10">November 10, 1960</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <list type="subject">
                    <head>SUBJECT</head>
                    <item>Minutes of Special Group Meeting, 10 November 1960</item>
                </list>
                <list type="participants">
                    <head>PRESENT</head>
                    <item>Messrs. <persName corresp="#p_MLT_1">Merchant</persName>, Douglas, Gray,
                            <persName corresp="#p_DAW_1">Dulles</persName>, <persName
                            corresp="#p_BRM_1">Bissell</persName>
                    </item>
                </list>
                <p>[Omitted here is discussion of other subjects.]</p>
                <p rend="sectiontitleital">7. Contingency Plans for the Congo</p>
                <p>Mr. <persName corresp="#p_BRM_1">Bissell</persName> mentioned briefly that we are
                    making certain contingency plans for the Congo against the possibility of a
                    pro-Soviet <persName corresp="#p_LPE_1">Lumumba</persName> government, or
                    complications arising from a militant Katanga independence movement.</p>
                <p>Mr. Scott, who had replaced Mr. <persName corresp="#p_MLT_1">Merchant</persName>
                    in the meeting, said that the African Bureau of State agrees with <gloss
                        target="#t_CIA_1">CIA</gloss>’s general method of proceeding with these
                    plans.</p>
                <p>[<hi rend="italic">1 paragraph (11 lines) not declassified</hi>]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_PTA_1">TA Parrott</persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
